cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is about object detection, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning a flexible anchor mechanism, which is a machine learning task (cs.LG). The authors also mention the use of weight prediction, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method is evaluated on the COCO dataset, which is a popular benchmark for object detection and is often used in neural network experiments (cs.NE). Finally, the authors mention the potential for transfer tasks, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO).
